<br>
As far as what system your guild should use, I guess the easies answer would be whatever system the majority finds fair.  The point system is very fair, but requires more diligent monitoring and upkeep.  Officer decision is fair as long as it's based on fair factors like participation and whatnot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/umulrineweeple.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mulrine Weeple</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/15/01 4:45:03 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.amanda.dd.com.au/art/dragons/adoptions/animpatti.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: guild loot &quot;rules&quot;</span><hr size=1> Vivar what are you doing go make another twink so no body knows it is you and you can get a group.  <br>
