<br><i>"Pass me a beer this exp crap is over"</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/unephtu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nephtu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/15/01 3:23:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: guild loot &quot;rules&quot;</span><hr size=1> Fwiw, Imperial Guards is straight officer award on raids for bigger stuff (little stuff goes to the reagent fund for peridots, etc.)  On guild hunting groups, most everything except Velious quest gems is NBG to the group, then guild (Quest gems are tied to the ToV drops)<br>
<br>
The stickiest items to award are the ones that everyone can use - one of the worst I've been around for was a Hierophant cloak, which everyone in that group could use nicely - that one we randomed with everyone who didn't already have one rolling.  We simply couldn't decide who needed it most. <p>Nephtu <BR>
Dark Elf Reaver</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/16/01 6:25:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: guild loot &quot;rules&quot;</span><hr size=1> 1st Fist of Light's policy is that the highest level player <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>that can use it</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> (no alts) gets the item.  Absolutely no randoming allowed.  Exception is made if a member requests the raid for a specific item (ie quest item).  When someone gets an item, there is a hand-me-down guideline which <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  requests</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that the item being replaced be passed on to the next most eligible person.<br>
<br>
There've been no instances yet where more than one person is equally suited for the item drop.<br>
<br>
Edit: added emphasis to show that they don't just get every item but only a chance to upgrade.<br>
Don't mistake me presenting the way things are done for me supporting them.  I've attempted to have discussion on a point system to no avail. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A> at: 8/17/01 9:15:39 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ufaenyar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faenyar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/16/01 7:03:16 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ourplace.dhs.org/~gfoster/pics/Faenyar-Fishing.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: guild loot &quot;rules&quot;</span><hr size=1> That sounds pretty unfair to me (highest level present gets it)... that means that a person could potentially receive every single loot drop provided they showed up enough, with nobody else getting anything except the scraps that they *may* decide to hand down.<br>
<br>
I think my guild would riot if we did that.  I can just see the reaction now if I were to claim every single caster robe that dropped, just because I was the highest level present.<br>
